## 4. **What does fallingsand3d/fused_reorder.py look like?**\n**Does not exist.** There is no fused_reorder.py file.\n\n### 5. **What does fallingsand3d/world.py look like?**\n**Current state:** `world.py` is a complete World class managing all SoA arrays:\n\n**SoA Arrays allocated (all as CuPy arrays):**\n- **float4 arrays:** position (n,4), velocity (n,4), veleval (n,4), sph_force (n,4), color (n,4)\n- **float arrays:** density (n,), mass (n,), temperature (n,), health (n,), lifetime (n,), shear_rate (n,), exposure_heat (n,), exposure_corrode (n,)\n- **uint32 arrays:** packed_info (n,)\n- **uint8 arrays:** sleep_counter (n,)\n\n**Key methods:**\n- `__init__(max_particles=500000)` allocates all arrays\n- `resize(new_max)` reallocates (destructive)\n- `num_active` property counts non-DEAD particles\n- `spawn_sphere(center, radius, material_id, count)` \n- `spawn_cube(min_corner, max_corner, material_id, spacing)`\n- `kill_in_sphere(center, radius)`\n\n**Important:** `_high_water` tracks one past last allocated slot. DEAD particles have `packed_info=0`.\n\n**NO sorted_* temporary buffers are pre-allocated yet.** This is a gap that US-009 needs to fill.\n\n### 6. **What does fallingsand3d/physics/simulation.py look like?**\n**Current state:** `simulation.py` is essentially **empty** (1 line: only the docstring \"SPH simulation orchestrator.\"). The actual simulation pipeline has NOT been implemented yet.\n\nThis means:\n- No orchestration of Hash → Sort → Build → Step1 → Step2 → Integrate\n- No CuPy kernel loading beyond hash_sort.py\n- No simulation loop exists yet\n\n### 7. **List all Python and .cu files in fallingsand3d/**\n\n**Python files:**\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/camera.py` (orbit camera)\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/gl_cuda_interop.py` (GL-CUDA interop)\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/hash_sort.py` (grid hashing wrapper)\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/main.py` (entry point)\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/materials.py` (16 materials + interaction matrix)\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/simulation.py` (mostly empty)\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/__init__.py` (empty)\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/renderer.py` (point sprite rendering)\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/ui.py` (ImGui UI)\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/test_*.py` (5 test files: test_common_cuh.py, test_gl_cuda_interop.py, test_hash_sort.py, test_materials.py, test_world.py)\n\n**CUDA files:**\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/common.cuh` (shared structs, enums, constant memory declarations)\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/hash_sort.cu` (K_CalcHash kernel only)\n\n---\n\n## Key Findings for US-009 Implementation\n\n### Current Gaps:\n1. **No sorted_* temporary buffers** allocated in World class\n2. **No argsort/sort logic** implemented anywhere\n3. **No fused reorder kernel** (only K_CalcHash exists)\n4. **simulation.py is empty** — will be filled by US-014 (Full SPH simulation loop)\n\n### What Needs to be Built:\n\n**For US-009 to work, you need to:**\n\n1. **Add sorted_* buffer allocation to world.py:**\n   - `sorted_position`, `sorted_velocity`, `sorted_veleval`, `sorted_sph_force`, `sorted_color` (float4 arrays, shape (n,4))\n   - `sorted_density`, `sorted_mass`, `sorted_temperature`, `sorted_health`, `sorted_lifetime`, `sorted_shear_rate`, `sorted_exposure_heat`, `sorted_exposure_corrode` (float arrays, shape (n,))\n   - `sorted_packed_info` (uint32 array, shape (n,))\n   - `sorted_sleep_counter` (uint8 array, shape (n,))\n   - `sorted_hash` (uint32 array, shape (n,))\n   - `sorted_index` (uint32 array, shape (n,)) — the key for writeback in Integrate\n\n2. **Create hash_sort.py functions for sort:**\n   - `def sort_by_hash(hashes: cupy.ndarray, indices: cupy.ndarray) -> Tuple[cupy.ndarray, cupy.ndarray]:`\n     - Use `cupy.argsort(hashes)` to get sort permutation\n     - Return `(sorted_hashes, sorted_original_indices)` \n\n3. **Create a fused CUDA reorder kernel** (`physics/kernels/fused_reorder.cu`) or use fancy indexing:\n   - **Option A (fused kernel):** Single kernel that reads `sorted_index` once per thread, gathers all SoA arrays in parallel\n   - **Option B (fancy indexing):** Use CuPy's advanced indexing: `sorted_pos = pos[sorted_index]` for each array\n   - Option A is more bandwidth-efficient (preferred)\n\n4. **Wire it into simulation.py** (when US-014 is implemented):\n   ```\n   hashes, indices = calc_hash(unsorted_positions)\n   sorted_hash, sorted_index = sort_by_hash(hashes, indices)\n   reorder_all_arrays(sorted_index)  # gathers all arrays\n   # Now Step1/Step2/Integrate work on sorted_* arrays\n   ```\n\n### Architecture Notes:\n- **Double-buffer pattern:** After sort+reorder, physics kernels read from `sorted_*` buffers\n- **Integrate writeback:** Uses `sorted_index[sorted_i] = original_i` mapping to write final pos/vel back to **unsorted** arrays\n- **Next frame:** Hash reads from unsorted positions again\n- **Key pre-allocation:** All `sorted_*` arrays must be allocated at World init to avoid GPU memory fragmentation in hot path\n\n---\n\n## File Structure Summary\n\n```\nfallingsand3d/\n├── main.py                           (GLFW event loop, incomplete)\n├── world.py                          (SoA arrays, no sorted_* yet)\n├── materials.py                      (16 materials + interaction matrix)\n├── camera.py                         (orbit camera)\n├── renderer.py                       (point sprite rendering)\n├── gl_cuda_interop.py               (GL-CUDA interop via ctypes)\n├── ui.py                            (ImGui)\n├── hash_sort.py                     (grid hashing wrapper, calc_hash only)\n├── physics/\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   ├── simulation.py                (EMPTY — needs implementation in US-014)\n│   └── kernels/\n│       ├── common.cuh               (structs, enums, constant memory)\n│       └── hash_sort.cu             (K_CalcHash only)\n├── shaders/\n│   ├── particle